#. Tag: title
#: deployment_installserver.xml:12
#, no-c-format
msgid "Setting Up the Server Holding the Installation Sources"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: dm:docmanager
#: deployment_installserver.xml:14
#, no-c-format
msgid "<dm:bugtracker></dm:bugtracker> <dm:translation>yes</dm:translation>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_installserver.xml:19
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&productnamereg; can be installed in different ways. Apart from the usual "
"media installation covered in <xref linkend=\"cha.inst\"/>, you can choose "
"from various network-based approaches or even take a completely hands-off "
"approach to the installation of &productname;."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_installserver.xml:25
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Each method is introduced by means of two short checklists: one listing the "
"prerequisites for this method and the other illustrating the basic "
"procedure. More detail is then provided for all the techniques used in these "
"installation scenarios."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: deployment_installserver.xml:32
#, no-c-format
msgid "Terminology"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_installserver.xml:33
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In the following sections, the system to hold your new &productname; "
"installation is called <emphasis>target system</emphasis> or "
"<emphasis>installation target</emphasis>. The term <emphasis>repository</"
"emphasis> (previously called <quote>installation source</quote>) is used for "
"all sources of installation data. This includes physical media, such as CD "
"and DVD, and network servers distributing the installation data in your "
"network."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_installserver.xml:43
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Depending on the operating system running on the machine to use as the "
"network installation source for &productname;, there are several options for "
"the server configuration. The easiest way to set up an installation server "
"is to use &yast; on &sls; 11/&opensuse; 11.1 or higher."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: deployment_installserver.xml:50
#, no-c-format
msgid "Installation Server Operating System"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_installserver.xml:51
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can even use a Microsoft Windows machine as the installation server for "
"your Linux deployment. See <xref linkend=\"sec.deployment.instserver.smb\"/> "
"for details."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: deployment_installserver.xml:58
#, no-c-format
msgid "Setting Up an Installation Server Using &yast;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_installserver.xml:60
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&yast; offers a graphical tool for creating network repositories. It "
"supports HTTP, FTP, and NFS network installation servers."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_installserver.xml:67
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Log in as &rootuser; to the machine that should act as installation server."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_installserver.xml:73
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Start <menuchoice> <guimenu>&yast;</guimenu> <guimenu>Miscellaneous</"
"guimenu> <guimenu>Installation Server</guimenu></menuchoice>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_installserver.xml:80
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Select the repository type (HTTP, FTP, or NFS). The selected service is "
"started automatically every time the system starts. If a service of the "
"selected type is already running on your system and you want to configure it "
"manually for the server, deactivate the automatic configuration of the "
"server service with <guimenu>Do Not Configure Any Network Services</"
"guimenu>. In both cases, define the directory in which the installation data "
"should be made available on the server."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_installserver.xml:91
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Configure the required repository type. This step relates to the automatic "
"configuration of server services. It is skipped when automatic configuration "
"is deactivated."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_installserver.xml:96
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Define an alias for the root directory of the FTP or HTTP server on which "
"the installation data should be found. The repository will later be located "
"under <literal>ftp://<replaceable>Server-IP</replaceable>/"
"<replaceable>Alias</replaceable>/<replaceable>Name</replaceable></literal> "
"(FTP) or under <literal>http://<replaceable>Server-IP</replaceable>/"
"<replaceable>Alias</replaceable>/<replaceable>Name</replaceable></literal> "
"(HTTP). <replaceable>Name</replaceable> stands for the name of the "
"repository, which is defined in the following step. If you selected NFS in "
"the previous step, define wild cards and export options. The NFS server will "
"be accessible under <literal>nfs://<replaceable>Server-IP</replaceable>/"
"<replaceable>Name</replaceable></literal>. Details of NFS and exports can be "
"found in <xref linkend=\"cha.nfs\"/>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: deployment_installserver.xml:112
#, no-c-format
msgid "Firewall Settings"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_installserver.xml:113
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Make sure that the firewall settings of your server system allow traffic on "
"the ports for HTTP, NFS, and FTP. If they currently do not, enable "
"<guimenu>Open Port in Firewall</guimenu> or check <guimenu>Firewall Details</"
"guimenu> first."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_installserver.xml:122
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Configure the repository. Before the installation media are copied to their "
"destination, define the name of the repository (ideally, an easily "
"remembered abbreviation of the product and version). &yast; allows providing "
"ISO images of the media instead of copies of the installation DVDs. If you "
"want this, activate the relevant check box and specify the directory path "
"under which the ISO files can be found locally. Depending on the product to "
"distribute using this installation server, it might be necessary to add "
"additional media, such as service pack DVDs as extra repositories. To "
"announce your installation server in the network via OpenSLP, activate the "
"appropriate option."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: deployment_installserver.xml:135
#, no-c-format
msgid "Announcing the Repository"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_installserver.xml:136
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Consider announcing your repository via OpenSLP if your network setup "
"supports this option. This saves you from entering the network installation "
"path on every target machine. The target systems are booted using the SLP "
"boot option and find the network repository without any further "
"configuration. For details on this option, refer to <xref linkend=\"sec."
"deployment.remoteinst.bootinst\"/>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_installserver.xml:147
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Configuring extra repositories. &yast; follows a specific naming convention "
"to configure add-on CDs or service pack CDs repositories. Configuration is "
"accepted only if the repository name of the add-on CDs is preceded with the "
"repository name of the installation media, In other words, if you chose "
"<literal>SLES12SP1</literal> as repository name for DVD1 than you should "
"chose <literal>SLES12SP1addon</literal> repository name for DVD2. Same "
"applies to SDK CDs."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_installserver.xml:158
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Upload the installation data. The most lengthy step in configuring an "
"installation server is copying the actual installation media. Insert the "
"media in the sequence requested by &yast; and wait for the copying procedure "
"to end. When the sources have been fully copied, return to the overview of "
"existing repositories and close the configuration by selecting "
"<guimenu>Finish</guimenu>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_installserver.xml:166
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Your installation server is now fully configured and ready for service. It "
"is automatically started every time the system is started. No further "
"intervention is required. You only need to configure and start this service "
"correctly by hand if you have deactivated the automatic configuration of the "
"selected network service with &yast; as an initial step."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_installserver.xml:177
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To deactivate a repository, select the repository to remove then select "
"<guimenu>Delete</guimenu>. The installation data are removed from the "
"system. To deactivate the network service, use the respective &yast; module."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_installserver.xml:183
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If your installation server needs to provide the installation data for more "
"than one product of the product version, start the &yast; installation "
"server module and select <guimenu>Add</guimenu> in the overview of existing "
"repositories to configure the new repository."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: deployment_installserver.xml:191
#, no-c-format
msgid "Setting Up an NFS Repository Manually"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_installserver.xml:194
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This assumes that you are using some kind of &suselinux;-based operating "
"system on the machine that will serve as installation server. If this is not "
"the case, turn to the other vendor's documentation on NFS instead of "
"following these instructions."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_installserver.xml:202
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Setting up an NFS source for installation is done in two main steps. In the "
"first step, create the directory structure holding the installation data and "
"copy the installation media over to this structure. Second, export the "
"directory holding the installation data to the network."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_installserver.xml:210
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To create a directory to hold the installation data, proceed as follows:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_installserver.xml:214 deployment_installserver.xml:268
#: deployment_installserver.xml:316 deployment_installserver.xml:359
#: deployment_installserver.xml:680
#, no-c-format
msgid "Log in as &rootuser;."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_installserver.xml:219
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Create a directory that will later hold all installation data and change "
"into this directory. For example:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: deployment_installserver.xml:223
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"mkdir install/<replaceable>product</replaceable>/"
"<replaceable>productversion</replaceable>\n"
"cd install/<replaceable>product</replaceable>/<replaceable>productversion</"
"replaceable>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_installserver.xml:224
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Replace <replaceable>product</replaceable> with an abbreviation of the "
"product name and <replaceable>product_version</replaceable> with a string "
"that contains the product name and version."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_installserver.xml:231
#, no-c-format
msgid "For each DVD contained in the media kit execute the following commands:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_installserver.xml:236
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Copy the entire content of the installation DVD into the installation server "
"directory:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: deployment_installserver.xml:240
#, no-c-format
msgid "cp -a /media/<replaceable>path_to_your_DVD_drive .</replaceable>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_installserver.xml:241
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Replace <replaceable>path_to_your_DVD_drive</replaceable> with the actual "
"path under which your DVD drive is addressed. Depending on the type of drive "
"used in your system, this can be <filename>cdrom</filename>, "
"<filename>cdrecorder</filename>, <filename>dvd</filename>, or "
"<filename>dvdrecorder</filename>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_installserver.xml:250
#, no-c-format
msgid "Rename the directory to the DVD number:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: deployment_installserver.xml:253
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"mv <replaceable>path_to_your_DVD_drive</replaceable> DVD<replaceable>x</"
"replaceable>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_installserver.xml:254
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Replace <replaceable>x</replaceable> with the actual number of your DVD."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_installserver.xml:263
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"On &productname;, you can export the repository with NFS using &yast;. "
"Proceed as follows:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_installserver.xml:273
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Start <menuchoice> <guimenu>&yast;</guimenu> <guimenu>Network Services</"
"guimenu> <guimenu>NFS Server</guimenu></menuchoice>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_installserver.xml:279
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Select <guimenu>Start</guimenu> and <guimenu>Open Port in Firewall</guimenu> "
"and click <guimenu>Next</guimenu>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_installserver.xml:285
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Select <guimenu>Add Directory</guimenu> and browse for the directory "
"containing the installation sources, in this case, "
"<filename><replaceable>productversion</replaceable></filename>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_installserver.xml:292
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Select <guimenu>Add Host</guimenu> and enter the host names of the machines "
"to which to export the installation data. Instead of specifying host names "
"here, you could also use wild cards, ranges of network addresses, or the "
"domain name of your network. Enter the appropriate export options or leave "
"the default, which works fine in most setups. For more information about the "
"syntax used in exporting NFS shares, read the <systemitem>exports</"
"systemitem> man page."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_installserver.xml:303
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Click <guimenu>Finish</guimenu>. The NFS server holding the &productname; "
"repository is automatically started and integrated into the boot process."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_installserver.xml:311
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you prefer manually exporting the repository via NFS instead of using the "
"&yast; NFS Server module, proceed as follows:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_installserver.xml:321
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Open the file <filename>/etc/exports</filename> and enter the following line:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: deployment_installserver.xml:325
#, no-c-format
msgid "/<replaceable>productversion</replaceable> *(ro,root_squash,sync)"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_installserver.xml:326
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This exports the directory <filename>/<replaceable>productversion</"
"replaceable></filename> to any host that is part of this network or to any "
"host that can connect to this server. To limit the access to this server, "
"use netmasks or domain names instead of the general wild card <literal>*</"
"literal>. Refer to the <systemitem>export</systemitem> man page for details. "
"Save and exit this configuration file."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_installserver.xml:337
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To add the NFS service to the list of servers started during system boot, "
"execute the following commands:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: deployment_installserver.xml:341
#, no-c-format
msgid "systemctl enable nfsserver"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_installserver.xml:344
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Start the NFS server with <command>systemctl start nfsserver</command>. If "
"you need to change the configuration of your NFS server later, modify the "
"configuration file and restart the NFS daemon with <command>systemctl "
"restart nfsserver</command>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_installserver.xml:354
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Announcing the NFS server via OpenSLP makes its address known to all clients "
"in your network."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_installserver.xml:364
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Create the <filename>/etc/slp.reg.d/install.suse.nfs.reg</filename> "
"configuration file with the following lines:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: deployment_installserver.xml:368
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<?dbsuse-fo font-size=\"7pt\"?># Register the NFS Installation Server\n"
"service:install.suse:nfs://$HOSTNAME/<replaceable>path_to_repository</"
"replaceable>/DVD1,en,65535 \n"
"description=NFS Repository"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_installserver.xml:369
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Replace <replaceable>path_to_repository</replaceable> with the actual path "
"to the installation source on your server."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_installserver.xml:375 deployment_installserver.xml:470
#, no-c-format
msgid "Start the OpenSLP daemon with <command>systemctl start slpd</command>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_installserver.xml:381
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"For more information about OpenSLP, refer to the package documentation "
"located under <filename>/usr/share/doc/packages/openslp/</filename> or refer "
"to <xref linkend=\"cha.slp\"/>. More Information about NFS, refer to <xref "
"linkend=\"cha.nfs\"/>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: deployment_installserver.xml:389
#, no-c-format
msgid "Setting Up an FTP Repository Manually"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_installserver.xml:391
