#. Tag: title
#: deployment_installserver.xml:663
#, no-c-format
msgid "Using ISO Images of the Installation Media on the Server"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_installserver.xml:665
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Instead of copying physical media into your server directory manually, you "
"can also mount the ISO images of the installation media into your "
"installation server and use them as a repository. To set up an HTTP, NFS or "
"FTP server that uses ISO images instead of media copies, proceed as follows:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_installserver.xml:674
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Download the ISO images and save them to the machine to use as the "
"installation server."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_installserver.xml:685
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Choose and create an appropriate location for the installation data, as "
"described in <xref linkend=\"sec.deployment.instserver.nfs\"/>, <xref "
"linkend=\"sec.deployment.instserver.ftp\"/>, or <xref linkend=\"sec."
"deployment.instserver.http\"/>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_installserver.xml:693
#, no-c-format
msgid "Create subdirectories for each DVD."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_installserver.xml:698
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To mount and unpack each ISO image to the final location, issue the "
"following command:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: deployment_installserver.xml:702
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"mount -o loop <replaceable>path_to_iso</"
"replaceable><replaceable>path_to_repository</replaceable>/"
"<replaceable>product</replaceable>/<replaceable>mediumx</replaceable>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_installserver.xml:703
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Replace <replaceable>path_to_iso</replaceable> with the path to your local "
"copy of the ISO image, <replaceable>path_to_repository</replaceable> with "
"the source directory of your server, <replaceable>product</replaceable> with "
"the product name, and <replaceable>mediumx</replaceable> with the type (CD "
"or DVD) and number of media you are using."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_installserver.xml:712
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Repeat the previous step to mount all ISO images needed for your product."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_installserver.xml:717
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Start your installation server as usual, as described in <xref linkend=\"sec."
"deployment.instserver.nfs\"/>, <xref linkend=\"sec.deployment.instserver.ftp"
"\"/>, or <xref linkend=\"sec.deployment.instserver.http\"/>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_installserver.xml:726
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To automatically mount the ISO images at boot time, add the respective mount "
"entries to <filename>/etc/fstab</filename>. An entry according to the "
"previous example would look like the following:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: deployment_installserver.xml:732
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<replaceable>path_to_iso</replaceable>&nbsp;<replaceable>path_to_repository</"
"replaceable>/<replaceable>product</replaceable><replaceable>medium</"
"replaceable>&nbsp;auto&nbsp;loop"
msgstr ""
